From 72cf85c646f39f693fe3ed4ceb200488ee081f44 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vivek Chettri <vchettri@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 4 Jul 2025 22:15:53 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] UPSTREAM: CP: wifi: ath12k: Add APIs to configure QoS

QoS Features like MSCS and SCS(legacy and 11be),requires QoS parameters
to be configured in the driver. The QoS parameters can be configured for
either Downlink(DL)or Uplink(UL) direction.

DL QoS parameters(legacy SCS/MSCS) could be just TID or
based on the 11be SCS specification, DL and UL QoS parameters,
can have multiple QoS characteristics elements like service interval,
burst size, min throughput delay bound and others.

For 11be SCS QoS parameters, DL and UL QoS profiles are created
to store all the QoS characteristics elements and assigned a QoS ID

For legacy SCS, only a QoS ID is assigned.

Following max profiles are supported
        QOS_DL_PROFILE_MAX(128) QoS profiles supported for DL
        QOS_UL_PROFILE_MAX(128) QoS profiles supported for DL

The following IDs are used for identifying the QoS Profiles *
        DL QoS Profile IDs      :   0 - 127
        UL QoS Profile IDs      : 128 - 255
        Legacy DL Profile IDs   : 256 - 263(one for each TID)

Add support to initialize the QoS context in the driver
and add the following APIs to configure QoS parameters.

        ath12k_qos_get_legacy_id
        ath12k_qos_update
        ath12k_qos_disable
        ath12k_qos_configure

Also add support for the following utility APIs
to get information related to QoS configurations.

        ath12k_qos_get_tid
        ath12k_qos_configured
        ath12k_get_qos

Signed-off-by: Vivek Chettri <vchettri@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Aishwarya R <aisr@qti.qualcomm.com>
